GLUT (GL Utility Toolkit)
- OpenGL was a strictly graphic API
- GLUT encapsulates the openGL so you don't have to worry about OS exclusive calls

- glutInitDisplayMode(GLUT_RGBA | GLUT_DOUBLE | GLUT_DEPTH); // store in frame buffer
- glutWindowPosition(0,0); // pixels from top left
- glutWindowSize(INIT_WINDOW_SIZE, );
- MainWindow = glutCreateWindow()
- glitSetWindowTitle()

Event driven Callbacks:
- glutSetWindow(MainWindow);
- glutDisplayFunc(Display);
- glutReshapeFunc(Size);
- glutKeyboardFunc()Keyboard;
- glutMouseFunc(mouse button);
- colormenue = glutCreateMenu(); // you can add menues to menues
- glutAddMenuEntry()
- AND MANY MANY MORE

Example:
	void keyboard(unsigned char c, int x, int y){...}
** Look this up Keyboard, mouse, menue and visibility

